The captain and Cythia decended into the lower decks down a long
ladder.  Once on the ground, it was aparent that the bad condition of
the bridge was not and isolated condition.  The large cargo room,
which had its enterance right off the hallway near the bottom of the
ladder, was littered with debris, empty and full cargo containers, and
miscelanous pot holes, burn marks, and other signs of some sort of
battle or severe turbulence.

After a quick glance around with a night vision scope, they decided
the room was empty and not worth investigating.  They turned and made
their way down the relatively wide corridor toward the holding cells
and the warden&#39;s office.

The emergency lights illuminated the warden&#39;s room, which was located
at the end of the hallway, though  these lights did little to lighten
the room.  Immediately upon entering, they noticed a large shadowy
figure in the corner of the room by one of the cells.

&quot;You there!&quot; shouted the captain suddenly, raising his weapon.  &quot;Name yourself!&quot;

The figure tuned around with loud echoing footsteps and slowly approached them.

